{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"d4b9f82f-7945-4cdf-8baf-6dc9bf25c851","content":"Yes, you'll run into compatibility issues. **MSTest v3 drops support for older target frameworks.** Specifically:\n\n- **`net462`** — MSTest v3 requires at minimum .NET Framework **4.7.2** (`net472`).\n- **`netcoreapp3.1`** — MSTest v3 requires at minimum **.NET 6.0** (`net6.0`). .NET Core 3.1 is no longer supported.\n- **`net5.0`** — Also unsupported; .NET 5 is out of support and MSTest v3 targets .NET 6+.\n\n### To migrate successfully you'd need to update your `TargetFrameworks` to something like:\n\n```\nnet472;net6.0\n```\n\n(or `net8.0` if you can target the latest LTS)\n\n### Summary of required changes:\n| Current TFM | Issue | Minimum for MSTest v3 |\n|---|---|---|\n| `net462` | Too old | `net472` |\n| `netcoreapp3.1` | Unsupported | `net6.0` |\n| `net5.0` | Unsupported | `net6.0` |\n\nIf you can't drop those older frameworks, you'll need to stay on MSTest v2. Want me to update the project file for the migration?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"58c87fcb-c7e1-4b49-b1ee-1a7df986c525","outputTokens":323,"requestId":"0412:19036B:16EC9B5:185CFD6:6A033806"},"id":"79e4376b-7953-4767-bd82-7361b4da4f24","timestamp":"2026-05-12T14:24:19.155Z","parentId":"3add3ff4-588a-4aee-ac9f-3783a8221586"}
